&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe&#39;s Marketplaces product team sits inside Money Management Services (MMS) and owns the financial infrastructure that marketplace platforms use to move money between buyers, sellers, and themselves. Marketplaces are structurally different from direct merchants: money doesn&#39;t just flow from a buyer to a single seller—it splits, routes, holds, gets reserved, crosses currencies, and arrives in dozens of countries through a chain of platform decisions. Getting that right, at scale and reliably, is the problem this team owns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connect platforms represent the majority of Stripe&#39;s pay-in volume, and the marketplace segment is our fastest-growing and most complex. The fund flow problem is not fully solved industry-wide; platforms still hit rough edges at scale around multi-currency, cross-border operations, and multi-processor reconciliation. By solving these problems, we create durable switching costs and make Stripe the obvious choice for the next generation of marketplace businesses. Our pod is a small group working intensely on bounded problems with high autonomy and high accountability. We ship via focused milestones, measure activation and revenue impact directly, and iterate fast.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly technical Product Manager to lead our Marketplaces product suite. This is not a generic PM role: you will work at the intersection of multi-party fund flows, cross-border money movement, platform controls, and the complex regulatory landscape that governs all of it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A significant part of this role is outbound-focused. You will bridge the gap between what a platform tells a sales team they need and what their engineers actually require to build. You will act as the central translator between a legal constraint, an engineering implementation, and a platform&#39;s business logic—co-designing APIs directly with flagship users and taking those validated solutions global.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage directly with flagship marketplaces to understand their charge types, transfer logic, payout schedules, reserve policies, and the edge cases they encounter at scale; synthesize these learnings to set product direction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Co-design and pressure-test APIs with reference users through structured early-access programs, including working directly with major marketplace engineering and finance teams on what is blocking their global expansion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain active relationships with flagship accounts to validate problem framing, and work closely with Enterprise Sales and Solutions Engineering to turn user learnings into durable product decisions that scale beyond the initial accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve core fund flow primitives—including debits and transfers—to make them more reliable, transparent, and globally available; build closed-loop wallet infrastructure for commercial marketplaces where buyers hold and respend balances&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expand cross-border payout coverage by unlocking more currencies, corridors, and faster settlement speeds for marketplace sellers without adding integration complexity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enable multi-processor fund flows, allowing marketplaces that process through multiple PSPs to make unified payouts via Stripe, including PSD3-compliant funding flows in the EU&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of product management experience, with at least 2 years focused on payments, fintech, or financial infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of shipping products across multiple teams while navigating significant technical complexity and strict regulatory or compliance constraints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable reading code, writing coherent specs, evaluating API designs, and contributing credibly to engineering discussions—without needing to write production code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong data fluency, including SQL, with the ability to form causal hypotheses about why metrics move rather than simply describing them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to build alignment across engineering, legal, and business functions to ship effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working at a two-sided marketplace or platform as a builder or operator, with firsthand understanding of multi-party money movement, seller onboarding, and reconciliation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Stripe Connect or equivalent platform-payment products (e.g., Adyen for Platforms, Braintree Marketplace, Hyperwallet, Payoneer)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing or improving financial reconciliation and settlement reporting for platforms or their sellers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of taking products from private or public preview to general availability, including driving self-serve activation and packaging and pricing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Program Manager for Agentic Commerce GTM, you will be the operational and coordination backbone of the highly cross-functional Agentic Commerce GTM motion. You will report to the Agentic Commerce GTM lead, but will work across a wide set of internal stakeholders including Global Partnerships, Enterprise Sales, Industry Sales, Solution Architects, Alliances &amp;amp; Channels, Professional Services, Marketing, and more. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will translate strategy into coordinated action, keep cross-functional partners aligned and accountable, and ensure that the GTM organization is operating with speed, clarity, and alignment as we scale merchant and agent ecosystem development.&amp;nbsp;You will have the opportunity to coordinate externally across both sellers (merchants/platforms) and agents as we stand up new pilot programs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the operating cadence of the Agentic Commerce GTM function, including driving weekly cross-functional GTM meetings like GTM SteerCo and pipeline.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as connective tissue across all GTM workstreams, maintaining a unified view of progress, blockers, and dependencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify process gaps or inefficiencies across GTM workstreams and drive improvements&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay updated on product developments to ensure GTM roadmap is aligned with product strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sharpen multi-party execution across agents and sellers to ensure Stripe delivers a first class experience and enables pilots and betas to graduate to scaled onboarding and eventual self-serve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive merchants towards integration readiness by coordinating across product, engineering, professional services, legal, sales, and more; proactively identify risks and help unblock&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage launch readiness for key agent partner launches ensuring our field, our partners, and our users are prepared for go-live&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Product S&amp;amp;O to define and track the right GTM KPIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain program tracking systems, dashboards, and reporting to give pipeline and progress visibility to senior stakeholders (e.g., RTBR)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with SSO and F&amp;amp;S to develop forecasts and drive planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in program management, sales operations, business operations, or a related GTM operations role — ideally at a high-growth technology or payments company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage complex, multi-work stream programs involving 5+ cross-functional stakeholders simultaneously, without direct authority&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills — you can synthesize ambiguous situations into crisp updates, and write clearly for both executive and working-level audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of building and running operational systems from scratch: project trackers, meeting cadences, reporting frameworks, and decision-making infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High ownership and accountability — you proactively identify what needs to be done and do it without waiting to be ask&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on GTM programs for emerging product categories — ideally AI, developer platforms, fintech, or payments infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with enterprise go-to-market motions, including partner/alliance programs, professional services, and solutions architecture teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building or scaling self-serve and scaled onboarding programs alongside a product team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical instincts — you can pull data, build dashboards, and frame problems quantitatively, even if this isn&#39;t your primary skill&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
